<subSubSection id="CBC06566FFB2FF9364BAFAE0FE20FA75" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="836536EDFFB2FF9364BAFAE0FE20FA75" blockId="2.[151,1127,1343,1558]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB2FF9364BAFAE0FEDDFAF5" bold="true" box="[151,268,1343,1366]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="44DA4D6EFFB2FF9365A6FAE0FE21FAF5" authorityName="Medvedev" authorityYear="1991" box="[395,496,1343,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Indostola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB2FF9365A6FAE0FE21FAF5" box="[395,496,1343,1366]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Indostola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by eyes not divided into upper and lower parts by genae; eyes in lateral view not diminished to narrow transverse stripe of facets in lower part (
<figureCitation id="1BE12A68FFB2FF93653DFAA0FE58FA35" box="[272,393,1407,1430]" captionStart="Figs 27–36" captionStartId="16.[151,188,1465,1484]" captionTargetBox="[185,1068,217,1444]" captionTargetId="figure-10@16.[185,1094,217,1444]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 27–36. Lateral view of head with eyes. 27 – Indostola pulchella Medvedev, 1991. 28 – I. kaengkrachanensis sp. nov.29 – Indochillus cristatus Koch, 1941. 30 – Pseudochillus (Pseudochillus) bangaloreanus (Kaszab, 1981). 31 – P. (P.) aalbui sp. nov. 32 – P.(Kaszabochillus) andamanus (Kaszab, 1981). 33 – P.(K.) helferi sp. nov. 34 – Pseudochillus (Micropseudochillus) palawanus sp. nov. 35 – P.(M.) thailandicus sp. nov. 36 – P.(M.) indochinensis sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304659/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Figs 27–28</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName id="44DA4D6EFFB2FF9365E1FAA0FD60FA35" authority="Herbst, 1799" authorityName="Herbst" authorityYear="1799" box="[460,689,1407,1430]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Stenosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB2FF9365E1FAA0FDF2FA35" box="[460,547,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Stenosis</emphasis>
Herbst, 1799
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="E74B4B1CFFB2FF9366C5FAA0FC44FA35" author="MEDVEDEV G. S." box="[744,917,1407,1430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" pagination="101 - 124" refId="ref12965" refString="MEDVEDEV G. S. 1994: Novye dannye po sistematike zhukov chernotelek triby Stenisini (Coleoptera, Tenebrionidae). (New data on systematics of darkling beetles of the tribe Stenosini (Coleoptera, Tenebrionidae )). Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 73: 844 - 867 (in Russian, English summary). [English translation in Entomological Review 75: 101 - 124]." type="journal article" year="1994">MEDVEDEV 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1BE12A68FFB2FF9367B3FAA0FC3DFA35" box="[926,1004,1407,1430]" captionStart="Figs 17–26" captionStartId="15.[113,150,1465,1484]" captionTargetBox="[113,1088,220,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-14@15.[113,1088,219,1431]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 17–26. Antenna. 17 – Indochillus cristatus Koch, 1941. 18 – Pseudochillus (Pseudochillus) bangaloreanus (Kaszab, 1981). 19 – P.(P.) aalbui sp. nov. 20 – P.(Kaszabochillus) andamanus (Kaszab, 1981). 21 – P.(K.) helferi sp.nov. 22 – Indostola kaengkrachanensis sp.nov. 23 – I.pulchella Medvedev, 1991.24 – Pseudochillus (Micropseudochillus) palawanus sp. nov. 25 – P.(M.) thailandicus sp. nov. 26 – P.(M.) indochinensis sp. nov. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304657/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); pronotum longer than wide and distinctly narrower than head; tempora almost parallel for one eye length behind posterior margin of eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBC06566FFB2FF9364BAFA00FC61F9B5" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="836536EDFFB2FF9364BAFA00FC61F9B5" blockId="2.[151,1127,1343,1558]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB2FF9364BAFA00FED7FA55" bold="true" box="[151,262,1503,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Remarks.</emphasis>
The illustration of the elytra in 
<bibRefCitation id="E74B4B1CFFB2FF936678FA00FCDCFA55" author="MEDVEDEV G. S." box="[597,781,1503,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" pagination="557 - 570" refId="ref12909" refString="MEDVEDEV G. S. 1991: Novye chernotelki trib Stenosini i Cnemeplatini (Coleoptera, Tenebrionidae) mirovoy fauny (New Tenebrionid beetles of the tribes Stenosini and Cnemeplatiini (Coleoptera, Tenebrionidae) of the world fauna). Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 70: 557 - 570 (in Russian, English summary)." type="journal article" year="1991">MEDVEDEV (1991</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="1BE12A68FFB2FF93673BFA00FC83FA55" box="[790,850,1503,1526]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="4.[151,188,1547,1566]" captionTargetBox="[165,1065,220,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[165,1071,219,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–4. Dorsal view. 1 – Indostola pulchella Medvedev, 1991, holotype ♀, India (West Bengal). 2 – Indostola kaengkrachanensis sp. nov., holotype♂, Thailand.3 – Tagenostola albovillosa Koch, 1940,Vietnam.4 – Pseudethas thailandicus Fouquè, 2008, holotype ♂, Thailand. Scale bar = 4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304651" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304651/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) is not accurate, as in fact the elytra are narrowing gradually to elytral base (see 
<figureCitation id="1BE12A68FFB2FF9366FAFA20FCC5F9B5" box="[727,788,1535,1558]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="4.[151,188,1547,1566]" captionTargetBox="[165,1065,220,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[165,1071,219,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–4. Dorsal view. 1 – Indostola pulchella Medvedev, 1991, holotype ♀, India (West Bengal). 2 – Indostola kaengkrachanensis sp. nov., holotype♂, Thailand.3 – Tagenostola albovillosa Koch, 1940,Vietnam.4 – Pseudethas thailandicus Fouquè, 2008, holotype ♂, Thailand. Scale bar = 4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304651" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304651/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="219">
Fig. 
<quantity id="44229B08FFB2FF93672AFA20FCC5F9B5" box="[775,788,1535,1558]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="2" pageNumber="219" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in this paper).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
